result.title: 1987 - 1987 Centre for Environment, Fisheries & Aquaculture Science (Cefas) Irish Sea Plankton Survey - RV Cirolana 05/87
result.name: 1987-1987-centre-for-environment-fisheries-aquaculture-science-cefas-irish-sea-plankton-s-05-87
result.notes:
Surveys to target spring ichthyoplankton in the Irish Sea were carried out in 
1987, 1988 and 1989 (and linked to an earlier series of *Nephrops norvegicus* 
L. larval surveys between March and June of 1982 and 1985). In 1987 sampling 
was confined to the western Irish Sea. Ichthyoplankton samples were collected 
at each site on a planned survey grid. The data described here consists of the 
numbers of fish eggs and larvae (also *Nephrops* larvae) identified from the 
main net samples collected on the survey in May 1987, along with associated 
positional and ancillary data and volumes filtered.
